{
  "texts": [
    "Our objective is to estimate the density ratio w * k ðxÞ = p k ðxÞ=uðxÞ based on the observed samples.",
    "Specifically, the in-sampple data x from the local distribution with p k (x) > 0 results in w * k ðxÞ>0, while the OOD samples x with probability p k (x) = 0 leads to w * k ðxÞ = 0.",
    "Therefore, the clients can build density-ratio estimators to identify the OOD samples from the proxy dataset.",
    "Considering the property of statistical convergence, we use a kernelized variant of unconstrained least-squares importance fitting (KuLSIF) 29 to estimate the density ratio.",
    "The estimation model in KuLSIF is a reproducing kernel Hilbert space (RKHS) 50 W k endowed with a Gaussian kernel function."
  ]
}